	<h4>Resources</h4>
	<hr style="width: 100%; height: 2px;">
	<br>
<a href="http://www.ldraw.org/"><img alt="LDraw.org" src="images/LDrawLogo.png" style="border: 0px solid ; width: 89px; height: 60px;"></a><br>
<h4><a href="http://www.ldraw.org/">LDraw.org</a></h4>
<font size="-1">Learn about the LDraw library of virtual Lego
bricks, upon which Bricksmith is based.<br>
</font>
<hr style="width: 100%; height: 2px;">
<h4><a href="http://www.kclague.net/LPub4.htm">LPub</a><br>
</h4>

<font size="-1">Make printed instructions from your models.</font><font size="-1"><br>
</font>
<hr style="width: 100%; height: 2px;">
<h4><a href="http://ldview.sourceforge.net/">LDView</a><br>
</h4>

<font size="-1">Fly through your models and export them to</font><font size="-1">
POV-Ray raytracer format</font><font size="-1">.<br>
</font>
<hr style="width: 100%; height: 2px;">
<h4><a href="http://james.magnusviri.com/lego/downloads/l3p.html">L3P
Launcher</a><br>
</h4>
<font size="-1"> Graphical front-end for <a href="http://www.hassings.dk/l3/l3p.html">L3P</a>, another</font><font size="-1">
POV-Ray converter</font><font size="-1">.<br>
</font>
<hr style="width: 100%; height: 2px;">
<h4><a href="http://www.povray.org/">POV-Ray</a></h4>
<font size="-1"> Turn your LDraw models into beautiful 3D
renderings with this raytracer.<br>
</font>
<hr style="width: 100%; height: 2px;">
<h4><a href="LSynth.html"><span style="text-decoration: underline;">LSynth</span></a><br>
</h4>
<font size="-1">Add fiendishly complicated flexible hoses to your
creations.<br>
</font>
<hr style="width: 100%; height: 2px;">
<h4><a href="http://ldraw.org/wiki/index.php?title=Macintosh_compatible_LDraw_software"><span style="text-decoration: underline;">Other Mac LDraw Software</span></a><br>
</h4>

<font size="-1">There's quite a long list these days.<br>
</font>
<hr style="width: 100%; height: 2px;">
<h4><a href="http://www.antonraves.com/welcome.php">Anton Raves<br>
</a></h4>
<font size="-1">Offers another POV-Ray converter based on his own part
library.<br>
</font>
<hr style="width: 100%; height: 2px;"><font size="-1"> </font><a href="http://sourceforge.net"><img style="border: 0px solid ; width: 88px; height: 31px;" alt="SourceForge.net Logo" src="http://sourceforge.net/sflogo.php?group_id=145754&amp;amp;type=2"></a><br>
<font size="-1"><a href="http://sourceforge.net/projects/bricksmith/">The
Bricksmith Project</a> is an open-source venture.</font><br>
</div>






<div id="mainbodybox">Bricksmith allows you to create
virtual instructions for your Lego creations on your Mac. The magic is
based on the <a href="http://www.ldraw.org/">LDraw</a> library, a
collection
of 3D models of Lego building blocks created by enthusiasts from around
the world. With Bricksmith, you'll never have to worry about running out
of parts!<img alt="Photon Chaser" src="images/PhotonChaser.png" style="width: 454px; height: 277px;" align="right" vspace="12"><br>
<br> Bricksmith offers:<br>
<ul>
  <li>drag-and-drop building</li>
  <li>thousands of parts at your fingertips, with no limitations on which ones you can use<br>
  </li>

  <li>a full Lego color palette</li>
  <li>support for steps and submodels, to document exactly how to build your creation<br>
</li>
  
  <li>undo, cut, copy, and paste</li>

  
  <li>multiple viewports<br>
  </li>
  <li>a <a href="MinifigureGenerator.html">Minifigure Generator</a><br>
  </li>
</ul>
Soak in the wonderment. View the <a href="images/screenshot.jpg">screenshot</a>.<br>
<br>
<br>
<br>
<br>
